title: Watch: Super Junior’s Yesung And Ali Release MV For Duet “You Are Not Here”
text:
Display.Sharethrough.Soompi.1x1 
Good friends Yesung of Super Junior and Ali have now released their new duet! 
The music video for the pair’s track “You Are Not Here” was shared on February 24 at midnight KST, and it features the two talented singers in separate shots as they play two people who are reflecting sadly on the loss of a past relationship. 
Yesung made his debut as a member of Super Junior in 2005, and has showcased his voice as a member of the group’s vocal sub-unit Super Junior K.R.Y, by releasing many successful OSTs, and through his solo debut mini album “Here I Am” in 2016. 
Singer-songwriter Ali has released several mini albums and albums, as well as lent her voice to OSTs. This is the duo’s second track together, as Yesung and Ali previously collaborated on a song entitled “Melody for You” along with Lee Se Jun and N.CA in 2016. 
What do you think of Yesung and Ali’s new duet?
